{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place water into mixing bowl and insert simmering basket. Place eggs into it and cook <nobr>10 min\/120°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set eggs aside to cool. Dry mixing bowl.","Place onion, garlic, ginger and chillies into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add ghee, ground turmeric, garam masala, salt and pepper and cook <nobr>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add coconut milk and cook <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>, then blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>-<strong>9, gradually increasing from speed 4 to speed 9<\/strong>.","When cool enough to handle, peel eggs, keep whole or cut into halves. Transfer eggs into a serving bowl and pour over coconut curry sauce. Top with coriander leaves and fried shallots before serving (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g water","8 whole eggs, room temperature (see Tips)","150 g brown onion, cut into quarters","2 garlic cloves","5 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","2 fresh long red chillies, trimmed and cut into halves","20 g ghee (see Tips)","½ tsp ground turmeric","1 tsp garam masala","½ - 1 tsp salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper","400 g coconut milk","fried shallots, to serve","fresh coriander leaves, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r256223","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-yo3fOJ066_U\/XZVPzN7o_lI\/AAAAAAAAc8s\/hQY0En4JENAQOY42BO6fQZiofzn2OUUOgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FR2tgQRXEjnNRrj6.png","title":"Eggs with coconut curry sauce","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.7 g","fat":"32.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"6.8 g","calories":"1624.6 kJ \/ 386.8 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Using cold eggs from the refrigerator will increase the cooking time. We used X-Large eggs (59 g) in this recipe; using smaller eggs will reduce the cooking time. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for timings for both soft and hard boiled eggs. Take care when peeling soft boiled eggs.","You can replace the ghee with oil of choice.","Serve with rice, if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","4 portions"]}